Durban - A 70-year-old Bluff resident is in a critical condition after he shot in a home robbery on Tuesday. Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, said the wife heard a loud bang at 4am and when she went to investigate she saw a man standing in the passage. "He instructed her to lie down on the floor. She managed to get away and pressed the panic button. The man fled the scene when the alarm went off. She then noticed her husband had been shot on the upper body," Zwane said. Garrith Jamieson, Rescue Care Paramedics spokesperson, said that the husband was seriously injured. He said when paramedics arrived at the scene they found the husband with a gunshot wound to his upper chest. "He was in a critical condition. We stabilised him before transporting him to a hospital," Jamieson said. A case of attempted murder was opened at Brighton Beach police station for investigation. Daily News 